.TH "tsi721_maint_dma" 9 "tsi721_maint_dma" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tsi721_maint_dma \- Helper function to generate RapidIO maintenance transactions using designated Tsi721 DMA channel.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tsi721_maint_dma
.BI "(struct tsi721_device *priv "  ","
.BI "u32 sys_size "  ","
.BI "u16 destid "  ","
.BI "u8 hopcount "  ","
.BI "u32 offset "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "u32 *data "  ","
.BI "int do_wr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "priv" 12
pointer to tsi721 private data
.IP "sys_size" 12
RapdiIO transport system size
.IP "destid" 12
Destination ID of transaction
.IP "hopcount" 12
Number of hops to target device
.IP "offset" 12
Offset into configuration space
.IP "len" 12
Length (in bytes) of the maintenance transaction
.IP "data" 12
Location to be read from or write into
.IP "do_wr" 12
Operation flag (1 == MAINT_WR)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Generates a RapidIO maintenance transaction (Read or Write).
Returns 0 on success and -EINVAL or -EFAULT on failure.
